<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" id="root">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>BlueArchival</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=M+PLUS+Rounded+1c&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/style.css?ver=yuuka">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/mobile.css?ver=yuuka">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/stylebar.css">
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.7.1.min.js" integrity="sha256-/JqT3SQfawRcv/BIHPThkBvs0OEvtFFmqPF/lYI/Cxo=" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <script src="assets/scripts/main.js?ver=yuuka"></script>
</head>
<body id="body">
    <nav>
        <div class="left">
            <img src="assets/millie.zone.png" alt="millie.zone logo" onclick="document.location = 'https://millie.zone'">
            <!-- <div class="splitter"></div> -->
            <!-- <div class="h2p" onclick="document.location = 'howtoplay'">How to Play</div> -->
        </div>
        <div class="right">
            <div class="admin" onclick="document.location = 'admin'">Admin</div>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <div class="top">
        <img src="assets/logo.png" alt="BlueArchival" class="logo">
    </div>

    <!-- <h2 style="color: red; width:100vw; padding:0; margin: 0;text-align: center;">THIS GAME IS A DEMO. IT IS NOT FINISHED.</h2><br>
    <h3 style="color: red; width:100vw; padding:0; margin: 0;text-align: center;">There are currently only 28 implemented students. All students will be implemented in the future.</h3><br><br> -->

    <h3 class="mobile">You are using a device with a small screen. This is not a first-priority experience. For the best experience, please use a device with a larger screen.<br><span style="color: rgb(18,138,250);">The C/D/I field stands for "City/Desert/Indoor" comfort levels.</span></h3>

    <div class="info">
        <h3>You get unlimited tries to guess the Blue Archive student.<br>Green means the category is correct. Red means it is incorrect. Orange means partially correct.</h3>
        <h4>See a full list of students <a href="https://bluearchive.wiki/wiki/Characters">here</a>. Use it lightly, like sorting students by school. If you want to sort everything, just turn on assist mode.</h4>
        <p>Enable assist mode?<button id="help">Off</button><a href="javascript:alert('this feature highlights characters that are compatible with what have figured out with your previous guess. example: if you guessed midori and her only shared feature with the student was that she is a 3-star, any other 3 star students will show as green in the search results.')">(what is this?)</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="share" id="share">
        <h2 id="final">You got it! The student was </h2>
        <button id="share-button" onclick="GenerateShare()">Copy Results (Blocks)</button>
        <button id="share-button-discord" onclick="GenerateDiscordShare()">Copy Results (Discord)</button>
    </div>

    <div class="search">
        <!-- first button exists solely for visual alignment -->
        <button>Enter</button>
        <input type="text" class="entry" id="entry" placeholder='Search Students (or type "hint")'>
        <button id="submit">Enter</button>
    </div>
    <div class="searchlist">
        <p id="did-you-mean">start typing to get results...</p>
    </div>

    <div class="list">
        <table class="student-tb table-toggled-on" id="students">
            <tr class="header" id="student-tb-header">
                <th>Student</th>
                <th>School</th>
                <th>Rarity</th>
                <th>Class</th>
                <th>Position</th>
                <th>Attack</th>
                <th>Defense</th>
                <th>Role</th>
                <th id="th-comfort"><img src="assets/images/city.webp" /> <img src="assets/images/desert.webp" /> <img src="assets/images/indoor.webp" /></th>
                <th>Cover?</th>
            </tr>
            <tr id="waiting"><td class="waiting">Waiting for first guess...</td></tr>
        </table>
    </div>
</body>
</html>